This paper proposes a hardware accelerator platform for on-device CNN inference for computer vision applications, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper focuses on energy efficiency, which suggests that it could also belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses transfer learning to train the models, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
